ce:section.ce:para:
In a L-LSC configuration, the substrate materials are the main components that act as waveguide for the propagation of re-emitted photons. In general, a good waveguide material should have a high transparency to allow the sunlight to pass through and reach the luminophores layer. A high refractive index (
                           n
                        ) is also crucial to trap as many emitted photons as possible inside the waveguides, decreasing the energy losses from the escape cone. The refractive index of substrate should be as close to that of the interlayer as possible to avoid reflection at the interface, which could lead to more reabsorption losses.
